title: Israel Sticks to Call for Gaza Evacuation and Readies a Possible Invasion
description: The United Nations and others condemned the call for more than a million people to leave northern Gaza, and Israel softened its initial 24-hour timetable.

title: How Hamas Overran Southern Israel and Killed 1,300
description: Hamas gunmen surged into Israel in a highly organized and meticulously planned operation that suggested a deep understanding of Israel’s military secrets and weaknesses. Here is how the attacks unfolded.

title: U.S. Tells World to Back Israel’s Gaza Strikes as Civilian Toll Rises
description: Secretary of State Antony J. Blinken is visiting the Middle East as the Israel-Palestinian conflict reaches a degree of violence not seen in many years.

title: Reuters Journalist Killed and 4 Others Injured Near Israel-Lebanon Border
description: Two journalists with Al Jazeera were also injured in the area, but it was not clear if it was from the same incident.

title: North Korea Shipped Arms to Russia for Use in Ukraine, U.S. Says
description: American intelligence agencies tracked a shipment of 1,000 containers of military equipment and munitions from North Korea to Russia, according to the White House.

title: Van Crowded with Migrants Crashes in Germany, Killing Seven
description: The accident followed a police chase near the Austrian border, where more smugglers are using vans or trucks to bring in groups of migrants.

title: ‘Start-Up Nation’ Is Tested as Israel’s Reservists Leave Their Desks
description: The tech industry in Israel, including many small firms, is trying to adjust as a big military mobilization cuts their work force.

title: Australia Likely to Reject Indigenous ‘Voice’ Referendum
description: The proposed Indigenous Voice to Parliament, widely supported by Indigenous voters but seen as likely to fail, has raised fears and hopes, both overblown.

title: C.I.A. Issued Warnings of Potential Gaza Flare-up Before Hamas Attack
description: Reports issued days before the Hamas attack did not foresee such a deadly strike, but did say rocket attacks were possible.

title: Protests in Support of Gaza Erupt Across the Mideast
description: Friday is a day of prayer in the Middle East, and this Friday was also a day of protest in support of the Palestinian people.

title: Behind a Senator’s Indictments, a Foreign Spy Service Works Washington
description: The charges against Senator Robert Menendez and his wife highlight how Egypt’s powerful intelligence agency wields influence.

title: Scenting Power, U.K. Business Flocks to the Labour Party
description: The governing Conservative Party was long seen as entrepreneurs’ natural ally and lobbyists’ most important target. With an election on the horizon, that’s changing.

title: Attack Kills 17 at Shiite Mosque in Northern Afghanistan
description: The attack was a bloody reminder of the insecurity that persists in the region and which has spread to neighboring Pakistan since the end of the U.S.-led war.

title: Russia Detains Lawyers of Jailed Opposition Leader, Aleksei Navalny
description: Attorneys for the jailed opposition leader, Aleksei A. Navalny, had been helping him maintain a significant public presence, even from prison.

title: Arab Citizens of Israel Were Killed in the Hamas-Led Attacks
description: About two million of Israel’s citizens are Arab. Many identify as Palestinian or share close family ties with those in the West Bank and Gaza.

title: Thousands Flee Gaza After Israel Orders Mass Evacuation
description: Some Gaza residents feared this was the start of another permanent displacement like the one in 1948, when more than 700,000 Palestinians fled or were expelled from their homes in present-day Israel.

title: At Least 1 Killed in Knife Attack at School in France
description: A suspect was quickly arrested after the attack, which French officials are treating as terrorism.

title: Israel-Hamas War: Panic Grips Gaza as Israel Calls for 1.1 Million People to Evacuate
description: The Israeli military demanded that Palestinians in northern Gaza move to the south as its troops mass on the border. The U.N. warned that the forced relocation would have “devastating humanitarian consequences.”

title: Fierce Fighting Flares Around Eastern Ukrainian Town of Avdiivka
description: Russia’s assault there may be a sign that Moscow is trying to regain the initiative in the war, after it spent months defending against Ukraine’s southern counteroffensive.

title: “Children Wading” Painting Returns to Glasgow Decades After Theft
description: Thieves in Scotland made off with the painting “Children Wading” in 1989. The work was recently returned after showing up at an auction house in northern England.

title: A U.K. University Will Confer a New Title: A Master’s Degree in the Occult
description: The postgraduate degree, to be offered at the University of Exeter starting next year, will focus on the history of magic, folklore and rituals.

title: Growing Wariness of Aid to Ukraine Hangs Over Polish Election
description: Last year, Poland was one of Ukraine’s staunchest supporters. But pressure from the right to focus more on domestic problems is pushing that support to the center stage of Sunday’s election.

title: Post-Punk Legend Leads Fight for Clean Water as Britain’s ‘Sewage Czar’
description: Feargal Sharkey, best known as the lead singer of the Undertones, has become one of the loudest voices demanding that Britain’s private water companies clean up their act.

title: A New Law Unites Northern Ireland — in Outrage
description: Catholics and Protestants alike say a commission created by the British Parliament to handle hundreds of sectarian crimes will do little to heal old wounds.

title: Israelis Rush to Volunteer and Donate After Hamas Attacks
description: A long-divided country is pulling together in a show of solidarity, donating everything from breast milk to high-tech help.

title: Friday Briefing
description: Israel calls on people in north Gaza to evacuate.

title: Why Are There So Many Jacintas?
description: The relatively uncommon name of Jacinta or Jacinda is shared among many famous people in New Zealand and Australia, with most of them born in the 1970s.

title: No Immediate Threat to U.S. Security Amid Hamas Call to Protest, Officials Say
E.U. Probes Elon Musk’s X Platform Over Violent Israel-Hamas War Content
description: Regulators are examining whether X violated a new European law that requires large social media companies to stop the spread of illegal content, disinformation and other harmful material.

title: Gaza Crisis Worsens as Israel Prepares a Possible Invasion
description: As Israel retaliates for the Hamas assault last weekend and plans a potential ground attack, its airstrikes have left Gazans without power, water and medical care.
